hormones that affect

00:01:17.440 --> 00:01:20.620 align:middle line:84%
our sex hormones,
testosterone, progesterone,

00:01:20.620 --> 00:01:22.460 align:middle line:90%
estrogen for men and women.

00:01:22.460 --> 00:01:25.360 align:middle line:84%
Then we've got a mess
with a hormone balance,

00:01:25.360 --> 00:01:27.880 align:middle line:84%
and it happened
really from stress.

00:01:27.880 --> 00:01:29.710 align:middle line:84%
Many other things
that it causes.

00:01:29.710 --> 00:01:32.980 align:middle line:84%
But we've got to remember
that our body's pretty smart.

00:01:32.980 --> 00:01:37.160 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes that stress in
a short period of time,

00:01:37.160 --> 00:01:41.410 align:middle line:84%
even if it's really high,
can be helpful for us.

00:01:41.410 --> 00:01:45.610 align:middle line:84%
>> What are some of the physical
effects of chronic stress?

00:01:45.610 --> 00:01:50.500 align:middle line:84%
>> Some of the effects of
chronic stress is your body

00:01:50.500 --> 00:01:53.590 align:middle line:84%
thinks it needs to run
from the bear all the time.

00:01:53.590 --> 00:01:56.050 align:middle line:84%
That it's in fight
or flight, and it

00:01:56.050 --> 00:01:58.750 align:middle line:84%
doesn't get into the
parasympathetic, which is

00:01:58.750 --> 00:02:02.260 align:middle line:90%
where we heal and repair DNA.

00:02:02.260 --> 00:02:05.590 align:middle line:84%
So when we're turned on
in that stress piece,

00:02:05.590 --> 00:02:08.740 align:middle line:84%
and literally telling
our body we're in danger,

00:02:08.740 --> 00:02:11.650 align:middle line:84%
all of those good things get
shut off for the sake of,

00:02:11.650 --> 00:02:13.030 align:middle line:90%
let's survive.

00:02:13.030 --> 00:02:15.520 align:middle line:84%
When we do that, it
causes inflammation,

00:02:15.520 --> 00:02:17.860 align:middle line:90%
the stress hormones rise.

00:02:17.860 --> 00:02:21.040 align:middle line:84%
>> Is it selfish to want to
take a break when you are taking

00:02:21.040 --> 00:02:22.960 align:middle line:90%
care of other people?

00:02:22.960 --> 00:02:26.380 align:middle line:84%
>> Self-care is not
something that you're doing

00:02:26.380 --> 00:02:28.510 align:middle line:90%
that's selfish.

00:02:28.510 --> 00:02:30.700 align:middle line:84%
How do you care for
others if you are not

00:02:30.700 --> 00:02:32.390 align:middle line:90%
caring for yourself?

00:02:32.390 --> 00:02:33.970 align:middle line:84%
Why do we think,
one of our tenants

00:02:33.970 --> 00:02:36.350 align:middle line:84%
as a physician is
physician heal thyself?

00:02:36.350 --> 00:02:40.880 align:middle line:10%
We have to learn not only how to
help ourselves to help others,

00:02:40.880 --> 00:02:43.540 align:middle line:10%
but we also have
to have the energy

00:02:43.540 --> 00:02:46.600 align:middle line:10%
to have the empathy and the
ability to care for others.

00:02:46.600 --> 00:02:51.220 align:middle line:10%
Social workers are high on
the list, my cancer patients.

00:02:51.220 --> 00:02:54.070 align:middle line:84%
